2026-04-20T05:25:58.971Z JOY-00F7-91 comment.added "Plan: 'joy project set acronym' migrates the local delegation directory atomically as part of the operation. Option (a) from the filing.\n\nChanges:\n1. crates/joy-cli/src/commands/project.rs: in the set_value path for 'acronym', before writing project.yaml, call fs::rename on ~/.local/state/joy/delegations/<OLD> -> <NEW>.\n2. Source missing -> no-op. Target already exists -> error, instruct the user to resolve manually; do not merge.\n3. Rename first, write project.yaml second. If rename errors out, acronym change is not committed.\n4. Unit test for the rename helper (source present, source absent, target collision).\n5. Integration test: project set acronym with pre-existing delegation dir moves it to the new path.\n\nAsymmetry to item IDs (which keep the old prefix per JOY-00F1-AD) is deliberate: item IDs are repo-visible, git-versioned artefacts with external references (commit messages, PRs). Delegation keys are local per-machine state read only by this tool, no external references." [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
