2026-04-20T17:29:45.655Z JOY-0104-D0 comment.added "Plan: Write tests/integration/attestation.bats upfront covering all 8 scenarios. Tests initially fail since the feature doesn't exist yet - they serve as the TDD contract for the subsequent child items. Each child item implements against them until all 8 are green.\n\nTest scenarios (mapped 1:1 to the 8-point attestation design):\n1. joy init creates founder without attestation\n2. joy project member add creates OTP + attestation signed by founder\n3. joy auth --otp sets passphrase and silently reverse-attests founder\n4. Subsequent joy project member add works without further reverse-attestation\n5. joy project member rm <self> blocked with manage-list error\n6. Manage removing another member inherits the removed member's attestations\n7. Manually injected member without attestation fails joy auth with clear error\n8. Tampered attestation signature fails joy auth" [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-04-20T17:31:59.195Z JOY-0104-D0 comment.added "[x] Wrote tests/integration/attestation.bats with 9 test cases covering the 8-point design.\n[x] Baseline run: 7 tests red (as expected), 2 pass for secondary reasons (will pass for correct reasons after implementation lands).\n[x] Tests serve as TDD contract for the remaining child items: implementation completes when all 9 tests are green.\n\nTest layout:\n- Scenario 1: founder-without-attestation invariant (1 test, currently green by default)\n- Scenario 2: member add -> OTP + attestation (2 tests)\n- Scenario 3: OTP redemption -> passphrase + reverse-attestation (1 test)\n- Scenario 4: subsequent adds do not re-attest founder (1 test)\n- Scenario 5: self-remove blocked (1 test)\n- Scenario 6: manage remove inherits attestations (1 test)\n- Scenario 7: manually injected member rejected at auth (1 test)\n- Scenario 8: tampered signature rejected at auth (1 test)" [ai:claude@joy delegated-by:horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
